# Review Chain

After `engineer` or `coder` completes a non-trivial change, invoke `reviewer` before presenting the result to the user.

## When to skip review

- Diff is < 5 lines.
- Diff is purely formatting / lint fix.
- User said "skip review" / "no review".
- Reviewer was already invoked in this session for the same files within the last 2 turns.

## Severity classification

| Severity | Action |
|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | Reviewer applies the fix immediately (security bug, data loss, broken test, broken build) |
| 🟠 Major | Original agent fixes; reviewer hands back with a list |
| 🟡 Minor | Note in report; not blocking |
| 🔵 Suggestion | Optional; do not block |

## Revision cap

- Maximum **2** revision rounds with the original agent.
- After round 2, if Major issues remain, escalate to `architect` instead of looping.

## Output

The reviewer's report is included verbatim in the user-facing summary so the user sees what was caught and what was waived.
